verses.text_plain: Concerning the Ammonites, thus saith the Lord; Hath Israel no sons? hath he no heir? why then doth their king inherit Gad, and his people dwell in his cities?
verses.verse_html:
1Concerning the Ammonites, thus saith the Lord; Hath Israel no sons? hath he no heir? why then doth their king inherit Gad, and his people dwell in his cities? ▼
▼ Concerning: or, Against
 , ▼
▼ their king: or, Melcom

footnotes.body_html: ▼ their king: or, Melcom

verses.text_plain: Therefore, behold, the days come, saith the Lord, that I will cause an alarm of war to be heard in Rabbah of the Ammonites; and it shall be a desolate heap, and her daughters shall be burned with fire: then shall Israel be heir unto them that were his heirs, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 2Therefore, behold, the days come, saith the Lord, that I will cause an alarm of war to be heard in Rabbah of the Ammonites; and it shall be a desolate heap, and her daughters shall be burned with fire: then shall Israel be heir unto them that were his heirs, saith the Lord.

tokens.text: that I will cause an alarm
and it shall be a desolate
unto them that were his heirs

verses.text_plain: Howl, O Heshbon, for Ai is spoiled: cry, ye daughters of Rabbah, gird you with sackcloth; lament, and run to and fro by the hedges; for their king shall go into captivity, and his priests and his princes together.
verses.verse_html:
3Howl, O Heshbon, for Ai is spoiled: cry, ye daughters of Rabbah, gird you with sackcloth; lament, and run to and fro by the hedges; for their king shall go into captivity, and his priests and his princes together. ▼
▼ their king: or, Melcom

footnotes.body_html: ▼ their king: or, Melcom

verses.text_plain: Wherefore gloriest thou in the valleys, thy flowing valley, O backsliding daughter? that trusted in her treasures, saying, Who shall come unto me?
verses.verse_html:
4Wherefore gloriest thou in the valleys, thy flowing valley, O backsliding daughter? that trusted in her treasures, saying, Who shall come unto me? ▼
▼ thy…: or, thy valley floweth away

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thy…: or, thy valley floweth away
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thy…: or, thy valley floweth away

verses.text_plain: Behold, I will bring a fear upon thee, saith the Lord God of hosts, from all those that be about thee; and ye shall be driven out every man right forth; and none shall gather up him that wandereth.
verses.verse_html: 5Behold, I will bring a fear upon thee, saith the Lord God of hosts, from all those that be about thee; and ye shall be driven out every man right forth; and none shall gather up him that wandereth.

tokens.text: from all those that be about
thee; and ye shall be driven out

verses.text_plain: And afterward I will bring again the captivity of the children of Ammon, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 6And afterward I will bring again the captivity of the children of Ammon, saith the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Concerning Edom, thus saith the Lord of hosts; Is wisdom no more in Teman? is counsel perished from the prudent? is their wisdom vanished?
verses.verse_html: 7Concerning Edom, thus saith the Lord of hosts; Is wisdom no more in Teman? is counsel perished from the prudent? is their wisdom vanished?

verses.text_plain: Flee ye, turn back, dwell deep, O inhabitants of Dedan; for I will bring the calamity of Esau upon him, the time that I will visit him.
verses.verse_html:
8Flee ye, turn back, dwell deep, O inhabitants of Dedan; for I will bring the calamity of Esau upon him, the time that I will visit him. ▼
▼ turn…: or, they are turned back

footnotes.body_text: ▼ turn…: or, they are turned back
footnotes.body_html: ▼ turn…: or, they are turned back

verses.text_plain: If grapegatherers come to thee, would they not leave some gleaning grapes? if thieves by night, they will destroy till they have enough.
verses.verse_html:
9If grapegatherers come to thee, would they not leave some gleaning grapes? if thieves by night, they will destroy till they have enough. ▼
▼ till…: Heb. their sufficiency

tokens.text: to thee, would they not leave

footnotes.body_html: ▼ till…: Heb. their sufficiency

verses.text_plain: But I have made Esau bare, I have uncovered his secret places, and he shall not be able to hide himself: his seed is spoiled, and his brethren, and his neighbours, and he is not.
verses.verse_html: 10But I have made Esau bare, I have uncovered his secret places, and he shall not be able to hide himself: his seed is spoiled, and his brethren, and his neighbours, and he is not.

tokens.text: and he shall not be able

verses.text_plain: Leave thy fatherless children, I will preserve them alive; and let thy widows trust in me.
verses.verse_html: 11Leave thy fatherless children, I will preserve them alive; and let thy widows trust in me.

verses.text_plain: For thus saith the Lord; Behold, they whose judgment was not to drink of the cup have assuredly drunken; and art thou he that shall altogether go unpunished? thou shalt not go unpunished, but thou shalt surely drink of it.
verses.verse_html: 12For thus saith the Lord; Behold, they whose judgment was not to drink of the cup have assuredly drunken; and art thou he that shall altogether go unpunished? thou shalt not go unpunished, but thou shalt surely drink of it.

verses.text_plain: For I have sworn by myself, saith the Lord, that Bozrah shall become a desolation, a reproach, a waste, and a curse; and all the cities thereof shall be perpetual wastes.
verses.verse_html: 13For I have sworn by myself, saith the Lord, that Bozrah shall become a desolation, a reproach, a waste, and a curse; and all the cities thereof shall be perpetual wastes.

verses.text_plain: I have heard a rumour from the Lord, and an ambassador is sent unto the heathen, saying, Gather ye together, and come against her, and rise up to the battle.
verses.verse_html: 14I have heard a rumour from the Lord, and an ambassador is sent unto the heathen, saying, Gather ye together, and come against her, and rise up to the battle.

verses.text_plain: For, lo, I will make thee small among the heathen, and despised among men.
verses.verse_html: 15For, lo, I will make thee small among the heathen, and despised among men.

verses.text_plain: Thy terribleness hath deceived thee, and the pride of thine heart, O thou that dwellest in the clefts of the rock, that holdest the height of the hill: though thou shouldest make thy nest as high as the eagle, I will bring thee down from thence, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 16Thy terribleness hath deceived thee, and the pride of thine heart, O thou that dwellest in the clefts of the rock, that holdest the height of the hill: though thou shouldest make thy nest as high as the eagle, I will bring thee down from thence, saith the Lord.

tokens.text: though thou shouldest make thy nest

verses.text_plain: Also Edom shall be a desolation: every one that goeth by it shall be astonished, and shall hiss at all the plagues thereof.
verses.verse_html: 17Also Edom shall be a desolation: every one that goeth by it shall be astonished, and shall hiss at all the plagues thereof.

verses.text_plain: As in the overthrow of Sodom and Gomorrah and the neighbour cities thereof, saith the Lord, no man shall abide there, neither shall a son of man dwell in it.
verses.verse_html: 18As in the overthrow of Sodom and Gomorrah and the neighbour cities thereof, saith the Lord, no man shall abide there, neither shall a son of man dwell in it.

verses.text_plain: Behold, he shall come up like a lion from the swelling of Jordan against the habitation of the strong: but I will suddenly make him run away from her: and who is a chosen man, that I may appoint over her? for who is like me? and who will appoint me the time? and who is that shepherd that will stand before me?
verses.verse_html:
19Behold, he shall come up like a lion from the swelling of Jordan against the habitation of the strong: but I will suddenly make him run away from her: and who is a chosen man, that I may appoint over her? for who is like me? and who will appoint me the time? and who is that shepherd that will stand before me? ▼
▼ appoint me…: or, convent me in judgment?

tokens.text: like me? and who will appoint me the time

footnotes.body_text: ▼ appoint me…: or, convent me in judgment?
footnotes.body_html: ▼ appoint me…: or, convent me in judgment?

verses.text_plain: Therefore hear the counsel of the Lord, that he hath taken against Edom; and his purposes, that he hath purposed against the inhabitants of Teman: Surely the least of the flock shall draw them out: surely he shall make their habitations desolate with them.
verses.verse_html: 20Therefore hear the counsel of the Lord, that he hath taken against Edom; and his purposes, that he hath purposed against the inhabitants of Teman: Surely the least of the flock shall draw them out: surely he shall make their habitations desolate with them.

tokens.text: surely he shall make their habitations

verses.text_plain: The earth is moved at the noise of their fall, at the cry the noise thereof was heard in the Red sea.
verses.verse_html:
21The earth is moved at the noise of their fall, at the cry the noise thereof was heard in the Red sea. ▼
▼ Red sea: Heb. Weedy sea

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Red sea: Heb. Weedy sea

verses.text_plain: Behold, he shall come up and fly as the eagle, and spread his wings over Bozrah: and at that day shall the heart of the mighty men of Edom be as the heart of a woman in her pangs.
verses.verse_html: 22Behold, he shall come up and fly as the eagle, and spread his wings over Bozrah: and at that day shall the heart of the mighty men of Edom be as the heart of a woman in her pangs.

verses.text_plain: Concerning Damascus. Hamath is confounded, and Arpad: for they have heard evil tidings: they are fainthearted; there is sorrow on the sea; it cannot be quiet.
verses.verse_html:
23Concerning Damascus. Hamath is confounded, and Arpad: for they have heard evil tidings: they are fainthearted; there is sorrow on the sea; it cannot be quiet. ▼
▼ fainthearted: Heb. melted
 , ▼
▼ on…: or, as on the sea

footnotes.body_text: ▼ on…: or, as on the sea
footnotes.body_html: ▼ on…: or, as on the sea

verses.text_plain: Damascus is waxed feeble, and turneth herself to flee, and fear hath seized on her: anguish and sorrows have taken her, as a woman in travail.
verses.verse_html: 24Damascus is waxed feeble, and turneth herself to flee, and fear hath seized on her: anguish and sorrows have taken her, as a woman in travail.

tokens.text: her, as a woman in travail

verses.text_plain: How is the city of praise not left, the city of my joy!
verses.verse_html: 25How is the city of praise not left, the city of my joy!

verses.text_plain: Therefore her young men shall fall in her streets, and all the men of war shall be cut off in that day, saith the Lord of hosts.
verses.verse_html: 26Therefore her young men shall fall in her streets, and all the men of war shall be cut off in that day, saith the Lord of hosts.

verses.text_plain: And I will kindle a fire in the wall of Damascus, and it shall consume the palaces of Ben–hadad.
verses.verse_html: 27And I will kindle a fire in the wall of Damascus, and it shall consume the palaces of Ben–hadad.

verses.text_plain: Concerning Kedar, and concerning the kingdoms of Hazor, which Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon shall smite, thus saith the Lord; Arise ye, go up to Kedar, and spoil the men of the east.
verses.verse_html: 28Concerning Kedar, and concerning the kingdoms of Hazor, which Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon shall smite, thus saith the Lord; Arise ye, go up to Kedar, and spoil the men of the east.

verses.text_plain: Their tents and their flocks shall they take away: they shall take to themselves their curtains, and all their vessels, and their camels; and they shall cry unto them, Fear is on every side.
verses.verse_html: 29Their tents and their flocks shall they take away: they shall take to themselves their curtains, and all their vessels, and their camels; and they shall cry unto them, Fear is on every side.

verses.text_plain: Flee, get you far off, dwell deep, O ye inhabitants of Hazor, saith the Lord; for Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon hath taken counsel against you, and hath conceived a purpose against you.
verses.verse_html:
30Flee, get you far off, dwell deep, O ye inhabitants of Hazor, saith the Lord; for Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon hath taken counsel against you, and hath conceived a purpose against you. ▼
▼ get…: Heb. flit greatly

footnotes.body_html: ▼ get…: Heb. flit greatly

verses.text_plain: Arise, get you up unto the wealthy nation, that dwelleth without care, saith the Lord, which have neither gates nor bars, which dwell alone.
verses.verse_html:
31Arise, get you up unto the wealthy nation, that dwelleth without care, saith the Lord, which have neither gates nor bars, which dwell alone. ▼
▼ wealthy: or, that is at ease

footnotes.body_text: ▼ wealthy: or, that is at ease
footnotes.body_html: ▼ wealthy: or, that is at ease

verses.text_plain: And their camels shall be a booty, and the multitude of their cattle a spoil: and I will scatter into all winds them that are in the utmost corners; and I will bring their calamity from all sides thereof, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
32And their camels shall be a booty, and the multitude of their cattle a spoil: and I will scatter into all winds them that are in the utmost corners; and I will bring their calamity from all sides thereof, saith the Lord. ▼
▼ in…: Heb. cut off into corners, or, that have the corners of their hair polled

verses.text_plain: And Hazor shall be a dwelling for dragons, and a desolation for ever: there shall no man abide there, nor any son of man dwell in it.
verses.verse_html: 33And Hazor shall be a dwelling for dragons, and a desolation for ever: there shall no man abide there, nor any son of man dwell in it.

verses.text_plain: The word of the Lord that came to Jeremiah the prophet against Elam in the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah king of Judah, saying,
verses.verse_html: 34The word of the Lord that came to Jeremiah the prophet against Elam in the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah king of Judah, saying,

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord of hosts; Behold, I will break the bow of Elam, the chief of their might.
verses.verse_html: 35Thus saith the Lord of hosts; Behold, I will break the bow of Elam, the chief of their might.

verses.text_plain: And upon Elam will I bring the four winds from the four quarters of heaven, and will scatter them toward all those winds; and there shall be no nation whither the outcasts of Elam shall not come.
verses.verse_html: 36And upon Elam will I bring the four winds from the four quarters of heaven, and will scatter them toward all those winds; and there shall be no nation whither the outcasts of Elam shall not come.

tokens.text: and there shall be no nation

verses.text_plain: For I will cause Elam to be dismayed before their enemies, and before them that seek their life: and I will bring evil upon them, even my fierce anger, saith the Lord; and I will send the sword after them, till I have consumed them:
verses.verse_html: 37For I will cause Elam to be dismayed before their enemies, and before them that seek their life: and I will bring evil upon them, even my fierce anger, saith the Lord; and I will send the sword after them, till I have consumed them:

verses.text_plain: And I will set my throne in Elam, and will destroy from thence the king and the princes, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 38And I will set my throne in Elam, and will destroy from thence the king and the princes, saith the Lord.

verses.text_plain: But it shall come to pass in the latter days, that I will bring again the captivity of Elam, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 39But it shall come to pass in the latter days, that I will bring again the captivity of Elam, saith the Lord.
